The ability of individuals to work with data and operationalised ethical boundaries.
The availability and quality of data and the tools for working with it ethically.
The clarity of guidance on how to work with data according to internal policy and external regulation.
The diversity of participation in product design and the psychological safety required to raise ethical challenges.
The alignment of a businesss objectives and the rights of individuals.
A teams human and technical competency for working with data, creating software and securing its systems.
The ability to effectively work with data to inform decision making, algorithms and all the relevant trade-offs.
The awareness of the positive and negative impact on the lives of individuals, as a result of data based products and decisions.
The organizations principles, and its approach to the opportunity and risks related to using and commercialising data.
The way in which the organization is structured to effectively work with data and ensure accountability.
The organizations awareness of the long term impact of its work on society and the way in which it is perceived by the public.
How an organization communicates its data use policies, and its willingness to receive feedback.
